#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:230
msgid "Help & Information"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:231
msgid "The MLX Back In Stock Notifier automatically adds a \"Notify Me\" button to any out-of-stock product."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:233
msgid "How it works:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:235
msgid "Users click the button to join the waitlist."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:236
msgid "When you update the product inventory to \"In Stock\", the plugin queues an email to everyone on the list."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:237
msgid "You can use the \"Waitlists\" tab to manually suggest alternative products to users who are waiting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:240
msgid "Background Processing (Action Scheduler)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:241
msgid "To ensure your website never slows down or crashes, all emails (both automatic restocks and manual alternative suggestions) are processed in the background using WooCommerce's native Action Scheduler."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:250
#, php-format
msgid "If you have hundreds of users waiting, emails will be sent safely in batches over a few minutes. You can view the status of pending emails by going to <a href=\"%s\">WooCommerce > Status > Scheduled Actions</a>."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:261
msgid "If you notice any failed actions, it usually means your server had a temporary issue sending an email. You can retry failed actions from the Scheduled Actions page, and they will be re-queued for processing."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:263
msgid "If you want to disable background processing for some reason, the plugin will still work but all emails will be sent synchronously during the page load that triggers them. This is not recommended for stores with more than a few waiting users."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:265
msgid "Email Deliverability"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:266
msgid "The plugin uses WooCommerce's built-in email sending functions, which in turn use WordPress's wp_mail(). To improve deliverability and avoid emails being marked as spam, the plugin sets the \"From\" name and email address to match your WooCommerce settings (or defaults to your site name and admin email)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:268
msgid "For best results, we recommend using a dedicated SMTP plugin to send your WooCommerce emails, such as WP Mail SMTP or Post SMTP. These plugins can help ensure your emails are authenticated properly and have a much higher chance of reaching your customers' inboxes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:270
msgid "Customizing Email Content"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:271
msgid "The automatic restock notification email content can be customized by using the \"woocommerce_email\" filter in your theme's functions.php file or a custom plugin. The manual alternative suggestion email content can be customized directly from the form on the \"Waitlists\" tab when managing a product's waitlist."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:273
msgid "If you need help with customizations or want to request a new feature, please contact us at modulux.net."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:275
msgid "Performance & Scalability"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:276
msgid "The plugin is designed to be lightweight and efficient, even with large numbers of waiting users. By leveraging caching for aggregate waitlist counts and using background processing for emails, it minimizes the impact on your server's performance."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:278
msgid "The waitlist management page uses pagination to ensure it loads quickly, even if thousands of users are waiting for a product. The alternative product suggestion form also uses WooCommerce's native AJAX product search to make it easy to find and select products without slowing down the page."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:280
msgid "Overall, the plugin should work well for stores of all sizes, from small shops with a few waiting customers to large enterprises with thousands of notifications to manage."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:282
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:283
msgid "If you are not seeing the \"Notify Me\" button on out-of-stock products, please check the following:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:285
msgid "Make sure you are logged in, as the button only appears for logged-in users."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:286
msgid "Check that the product is actually marked as \"Out of Stock\" in WooCommerce."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:287
msgid "Temporarily switch to a default theme like Storefront to rule out any theme conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:288
msgid "Disable other plugins to check for conflicts, especially those that modify product pages or handle notifications."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:292
msgid "The following CSS classes can be used to customize the appearance of the plugin:"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:316
msgid "To customize the plugin appearance, add these CSS classes to your theme's custom CSS or child theme stylesheet. This keeps the plugin lightweight without adding unnecessary admin settings."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:318
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:320
msgid "Regularly check the \"Waitlists\" tab to manage your waiting customers and suggest alternatives."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:321
msgid "When restocking products, try to update inventory in the morning or early afternoon to ensure emails go out during optimal open times."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:322
msgid "Use the alternative product suggestion feature to potentially save sales even if the original product is delayed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:325
msgid "Support & Contact"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-bis-admin.php:326
msgid "If you have any questions, need help with customizations, or want to report a bug, please contact us at <a href=\"https://modulux.net/\" target=\"_blank\">modulux.net</a>."
msgstr ""

